## TECHNICAL STANDARDS

**Stack**
- JSX with Tailwind CSS utility classes, React hooks, and Lucide React for icons.
- Do not install additional UI libraries, icon packs, or component frameworks unless 
  explicitly requested.
- Google Fonts via @import in CSS or link tag only — no font packages.

**Components**
- Split into clean, logical components. No single file god-components over ~200 lines.
- Props must have sensible defaults. No component should break when optional props missing.
- Name components clearly and semantically.

**Responsiveness**
- Every build is mobile-first. Design for 320px up, not desktop squeezed down.
- Thoughtful breakpoints: sm (640px), md (768px), lg (1024px), xl (1280px).
- Navigation always has a working mobile hamburger menu with smooth open/close animation.
- Touch targets minimum 44x44px on mobile.

**States — Non-negotiable**
Every interactive element must have all of these covered:
- Default state
- Hover state  
- Active/pressed state
- Focus state (keyboard accessible, visible outline)
- Loading state (where async operations exist)
- Error state (with clear human-readable messages)
- Empty state (where lists or data can be empty)
- Success state (confirmations, completions)

**Forms & Data**
- All form inputs must have visible labels (not placeholder-only).
- Inline validation with clear error messaging.
- Submit buttons must show loading state and disable on submission.
- All form submissions and webhook calls must be structured for Make.com compatibility:
  - POST to the webhook URL provided, or leave a clearly marked placeholder: 
    `const MAKE_WEBHOOK_URL = "YOUR_MAKE_WEBHOOK_URL_HERE"`
  - Send clean JSON payloads with descriptive key names.
  - Always handle the Make.com response and show appropriate success/error feedback.

**Images**
- Use picsum.photos for placeholder images: https://picsum.photos/[width]/[height]
- Add seed for consistency: https://picsum.photos/seed/[keyword]/[width]/[height]
- Always include descriptive alt text on every image.

**Accessibility**
- Semantic HTML elements throughout (nav, main, section, article, footer etc.)
- All images have meaningful alt text.
- All interactive elements are keyboard navigable.
- ARIA labels on icon-only buttons.
- Focus styles must be visible and styled (not browser default).

**Code Quality**
- No console.log left in production code.
- No commented-out dead code blocks.
- No TODO comments unless flagged to the user.
- Error boundaries around async or data-dependent components.

