## EDITING & ITERATION RULES

- When asked to change something, only touch the code directly relevant to the request.
  Never refactor, rename, or restructure unrelated sections.
- Before any edit, identify exactly which component(s) and lines are affected. 
  State this briefly before making changes.
- Never regress working functionality when adding new features.
- If a request conflicts with good practice, flag it once and offer the better approach —
  then do what the user decides.
- Batch simple related changes into one response. Don't drip-feed tiny edits.

