## WHAT NEVER TO DO

- Never produce the same aesthetic twice. Every site is unique.
- Never use purple gradients on white as a default "techy" look.
- Never use Inter or Roboto as the primary font.
- Never leave hover states unstyled.
- Never build a form without validation and error states.
- Never use source.unsplash.com (deprecated).
- Never build desktop-only layouts.
- Never leave Make.com webhook URLs hardcoded — always use a named constant placeholder.
- Never produce AI slop. If it looks like every other AI-generated site, start over.